# Line-ending normalisation. The repo is LF everywhere; `eol=lf` makes git store AND check out LF
# regardless of `core.autocrlf`, so a Windows clone cannot introduce CRLF that G52 (editorconfig-checker)
# would then flag locally. `text=auto` lets git auto-detect text vs binary. This file is L(-1)
# (scripts/l-neg1-files.toml, G71).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary / asset files: never EOL-normalise, never diff as text.
*.png  binary
*.ico  binary
*.icns binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.webp binary
*.pdf  binary
*.gz   binary
*.zip  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf  binary
*.otf  binary

# --- Corpus LFS tier (P1.4) -------------------------------------------------------------------
# §6 "[DECIDED] corpus storage": the small synthetic + CC0 fixtures under `tests/corpus/` stay real
# committed bytes (NOT LFS — the per-PR fast lane + the §6.4.3a bijection guard need them); the larger
# real-world media tier is LFS-backed under `tests/corpus-large/`, fetched only for the full Lane-B run
# (§6.7.2). The G24a corpus gate (P0.5.4) asserts every LFS-tier fixture is `filter=lfs`-tracked per the
# effective `git check-attr filter` (a tampered un-tracking edit then surfaces as a manifest mismatch).
# Reserved here; fixtures fill P3-P7 (exact homing reconciled against §0.7 as the corpus lands).
tests/corpus-large/** filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
